.TH GRAFANA-UTIL-DATASOURCE-INSPECT-EXPORT 1 "2026-04-03" "grafana-util 0.8.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
grafana\-util\-datasource\-inspect\-export \- Inspect a local masked recovery bundle without connecting to Grafana.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B grafana-util datasource inspect-export [\fIOPTIONS\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Inspect a local masked recovery bundle without connecting to Grafana.
.PP
Use this when you want to read datasource export artifacts from disk and review them with text, table, CSV, JSON, YAML, or interactive output.
.SH COMMON OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-\-input\-dir
local directory containing the export artifacts.
.TP
.B \-\-input\-type
select inventory or provisioning when the path could be interpreted either way.
.TP
.B \-\-interactive
open the local export inspection workbench.
.TP
.B \-\-table, \-\-csv, \-\-text, \-\-json, \-\-yaml, \-\-output\-format
output mode controls.
.SH EXAMPLES
.PP
Inspect a local masked recovery bundle without connecting to Grafana.
.EX
grafana-util datasource inspect-export --input-dir ./datasources --table
.EE
.SH SEE ALSO
\fBgrafana-util\fR(1),
\fBgrafana-util-datasource\fR(1)
